The navigation line is embedded in a (!T)<div>(!t) environment with the CSS class (!B)UDO_nav_line(!b). 
So you can format its content with CSS commands.

!item [(!EXAMPLE)]
(!T)!/html_navigation_line(!t) (!nl)
Chapter 1 > Chapter 1.1 > Chapter 1.1.1 > Chapter 1.1.1.1

!item [(!EXAMPLE)]
(!T)!/html_navigation_line ::(!t) (!nl)
Chapter 1 :: Chapter 1.1 :: Chapter 1.1.1 :: Chapter 1.1.1.1
!endif

